Inline Form:-
============

Ex:-
===

<html>
<head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Inline Form</h2>
    <form class="form-inline">
     <div class="form-row">
       <div class="col">
         <input class="form-control" type="text" placeholder="username">
     </div>
     <div class-"col">
       <input class="form-control" type"passsword" placeholder="Password">
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <button class="btn btn-primary">Login</button>
      </div>
      </div>
     </form>
    </div>
   </body>

Bootstrap Input Group
=====================

The Bootstrap input group allows group of set of elements into one category and align in coloumn the group is displayed as toolbar with collection of element the classes are:-

1) .input-group
2) .input-group-sm
3) .input-group-lg
4) .input-group-text
5) .input-group-prepend
6) .input-group-append


Ex:-
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Register User</h2>
      <form>
         <div class="form-group">
           <label>Email</label>
           <div class="input-group">
           <input type="text" class="form-control">
              <div class="input-group-append">
               <span class="input-grou-text">
             @gmail.com<\span>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
           <div class="form-group">
              <label>Website Page Address</label>
              <div class="input-group">
                 <div class="input-group-prepend">
                  <sapn class="input-group-text">
                  http://ww.blogger.com/</span>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                </div>
                </form>
               </div>
              </body> 
